{% layout 'layout.liquid' %}
{% block content %}
    <div class="container-sm">
        {%- comment -%}
        if a form, we have an action and a method
        the action points to our url endpoint
        the method is the http verb for that endpoint
        for example: this for will send a POST to /users/signup
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <form action="/users/login" method="POST">
            <fieldsest>
                <legend>Log in to your Account</legend>
                <label class="form-label">Username: </label>
                {%- comment -%}
                for inputs need a type(think data type) and a name (object key) so if we use type: String and require req.body.username, our form input will look like the one below
                {%- endcomment -%}
                <input type="text" class="form-control" name="username" placeholder="username" required>
                <label class="form-label">Password: </label>
                <input type="password" class="form-control" name="password" placeholder="password" required>
            </fieldsest>
            <input type="submit" class="btn btn-success mt-md-3" value="Log In">
        </form>
    </div>
{% endblock %}